<HEAD>Three Killed, 12 Injured in Building Collapse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rescue workers today cut through
concrete and steel to try to free two people trapped in the rubble
of a building whose collapse, according to police, killed at least
three people and injured 12.
   The three-story building, which was to be the offices of the
Buddha Pratheep charity foundation, caved in Sunday night on
construction workers living at the site.
   Dozens of soldiers, policemen and volunteers worked all night to
free 12 people, including a 1{-year-old boy, said Lt. Col. Nathee
Wongsathaporn, chief inspector of Phyathai police station.
   The dead were identified as a man, a woman and a five-year-old
boy who were believed to have been living on the ground floor.
