<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     09-12 0439</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0450</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow Falls in Wyoming Mountains; Rain Falls over Much of Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Rain fell today from northeastern Minnesota across the Plains to
Arizona, while a storm dusted Wyoming's northern mountains with
less than 4 inches of snow.
   Showers and a few thunderstorms also were scattered in the
central Gulf Coast states, the Tennessee Valley, the southern Ohio
Valley and central Mississippi Valley, and the Florida peninsula.
   Dry weather prevailed across the rest of the nation, with clear
skies over Washington state, Oregon, California, Nevada, Texas,
Oklahoma, Kansas, and much of New England.
   Temperatures were in the 70s early today from the southern
Plains through much of the Mississippi Valley to the southern
Atlantic Coast.
   Other readings: 30s in the northern Rockies; 40s and 50s in the
central United States, northern Atlantic Coast and Pacific
Northwest; 70s and 80s in the southwestern deserts.
   Today's forecast called for widespread rain and much cooler air
from the Great Lakes through the middle Missouri Valley into the
central Rockies; scattered showers and thunderstorms from the lower
Great Lakes into the middle Mississippi, lower Ohio and Tennessee
valleys; the central Gulf Coast and extreme southern Florida.
   Highs in the 70s or 80s were predicted across much of the nation
east of the Mississippi River; 60s or 70s west of the Mississippi;
50s in the northern and central Rockies from southeast Montana
through Wyoming and north-central Colorado into the Nebraska
panhandle and western South Dakota; 60s in northern Maine; 80s in
much of the Pacific Coast; 90s in California's northern and central
valleys and Oregon's valleys, the southern Plains and Texas into
the western half of the Gulf Coast; middle 90s in the desert
Southwest.
   The nation's temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 27 degrees
at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to 87 at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 73 partly cloudy; Boston 55 fair; Buffalo 50
partly cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 74 foggy; Cincinnati 67 fair;
Cleveland 60 partly cloudy; Detroit 57 fair; Miami 83 fair; New
York 59 partly cloudy; Philadelphia 59 cloudy; Pittsburgh 54 fair;
Portland, Maine 51 fair; Washington 63 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 47 windy; Chicago 72 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 81 fair; Denver 48 drizzle; Des Moines 67 fair;
Indianapolis 71 foggy; Kansas City 70 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 74
fair; Nashville 75 foggy; New Orleans 77 cloudy; St. Louis 73
partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 58 cloudy; Anchorage 49 rain; Las Vegas 73
fair; Los Angeles 62 cloudy; Phoenix 87 fair; Salt Lake City 45
fair; San Diego 67 cloudy; San Francisco 55 fair; Seattle 61 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 46 fair; Toronto 50 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
