<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Baltimore pigeon club will buy a grave marker
for a 12-year-old boy killed as he fell down an elevator shaft
while trying to catch pigeons.
   Keith Shipley and other boys had been trying to trap pigeons on
Aug. 24 when the boy tripped on a gate and plunged 12 stories down
the elevator shaft of a downtown parking garage, police said.
   ``Because of his love of pigeons and the whole unfortunate
situation of his childhood, the club would like to help out,'' said
Mike Fahey of the Hamilton Homing Pigeon Club. The 55-member group
voted last week to pay for the headstone, he said.
