<HEAD>Ramstein Death Toll Reaches 60</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: RETRANSMITTING to correct cycle designator</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MAINZ, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The death toll from the Ramstein air
show disaster climbed to 60 on Monday when a 28-year-old man died
of his injuries, West German officials said.
   Bernd Horion, a spokesman for Rhineland Palatinate state, said
the West German man died at a Ludwigshafen clinic, more than two
weeks after the world's worst air show catastrophe.
