hospitals in West Germany. A total of 156 people were hospitalized
in 46 clinics, he said.
   On Aug. 28, an Italian air force stunt team jet fighter collided
with two other Italian jets and crashed into spectators at the U.S.
Air Force base at Ramstein in southwestern Germany. All three
pilots were among those killed.
