<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A late-summer surge in gasoline prices fueled
wholesale inflation in August at a pace matching the highest level
of the year, even though food prices began recovering from the
drought, the government said.
   The Labor Department said Friday that its Producer Price Index
for finished goods rose a seasonally adjusted 0.6 percent last
month, the heftiest increase since an identical rise in March.
   If that rate held for 12 consecutive months, inflation at the
wholesale level would amount to 6.9 percent, more than triple the
2.2 percent price rise for 1987.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Roy E. Disney's Shamrock Holdings Inc.
went directly to Polaroid Corp. shareholders with a cash bid that
values the company at about $2.6 billion.
   Shamrock said Friday it would raise its new bid to $44 a share
from $42 if directors dropped their resistance to the takeover
attempt.
   Polaroid's board of directors last month rejected an unsolicited
offer from Shamrock that would have paid $40 a share plus 40
percent of the eventual award in Polaroid's patent infringement
lawsuit against Eastman Kodak Co. A percentage of that potential
settlement was not included in the new, hostile tender offer of $42
a share, which bypasses the directors.
