Copper-7 intrauterine device and misrepresented it, which was a
cause of the woman's sterility.
   The jury on Friday awarded Esther Kociemba, 30, of Elk River,
Minn., $7 million in punitive damages, $1 million for emotional
distress and $750,000 for pain and disability.
   The jury decided that Mrs. Kociemba's husband, William, did not
experience the loss of consortium as a direct result of his wife's
use of the Copper-7 and did not award him damages.
