<HEAD>Bayer USA to Merge Subsidiaries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bayer USA Inc., a subsidiary of Bayer AG of
West Germany, said today it will merge subsidiaries Agfa-Gevaert
Inc., Compugraphic Corp. and Matrix Corp. into one corporation at
the end of the year.
   Bayer USA said the new subsidiary, Agfa Corp., will be located
at Afga-Gevaert's current headquarters in Ridgefield Park, N.J.
Compugraphic Corp. is headquartered in Wilmington, Mass., and
