<DOCNO> AP880912-0244 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-12-88 1456EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f BC-GrandMet     09-12 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Grand Met,0147</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>EEC To Study Grand Met Complaint On Irish Distillers Bid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Economic Community
Commission will study a complaint by Grand Metropolitan PLC about
Pernod Ricard SA's bid to win control of Irish Distillers Group
PLC, an aide to EEC Competition Commissioner Peter Sutherland said
Monday.
   The complaint centers on irrevocable commitments Pernod says it
received for 51.8 percent of Irish Distillers shares before Grand
Met made its competing bid a week ago.
   Grand Met claims Pernod's and Irish Distillers' actions are
anti-competitive and violate the fair-trade rules of the EEC's
founding Treaty of Rome.
   The commission's antitrust division received the complaint
Monday.
   The aide to Sutherland said the commission will examine Grand
Met's complaint to see whether it is justified. This would involve
seeking comments from Pernod and Irish Distillers, he said.
</TEXT>
