<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Rose 0.2 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production rose to 1.921 million tons in
the week ended Sept. 10, an increase of 0.2 percent from the
previous week's 1.918 million tons, the American Iron and Steel
Institute reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 90.1 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 89.9 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
69.644 million net tons, an increase of 18.2 percent from the
58.918 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.6 percent of capacity,
compared with 75.9 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Sept. 10: Northeast
Coast, 273,000; Pittsburgh, 201,000; Youngstown, 93,000; Lake Erie,
155,000; Detroit, 162,000; Chicago, 536,000; Midwest, 195,000;
Southern, 215,000; and Western, 91,000.
